f=Engineering/aegis/custom/vuln-pipeline/SKILL.md · in=vuln-pipeline aegis's discovery engine: threat-model-scoped loop **recon find verify dedupe triage route** turns "where exposed" (the threat model) ranked, verified, owner-routed findings. runs static-first (read/write only, safe unsandboxed, like harness's Step skills); execution-verified finding (the harness's autonomous pipeline, Step 2+) runs **only** inside gVisor-pattern sandbox Security Charter's Rail generalizes harness. · p=Scanning without threat model finds noise; threat model without scanning wish. pipeline joins them: threat model (imported skill) scopes what look for, scan finds candidates, verification kills false positives (the harness's separate-grader-reproduces-the-crash discipline), dedupe collapses repeats, triage ranks against threat model, routing sends real finding owner. aegis defends; caged adversary (cypher) attacks defensive half. · wu=Triggers: "scan vulnerabilities," "run vuln pipeline," "find bugs [target]," "triage findings," new threat model landing, CVE arriving ops's maintenance-hygiene, risky-diff referral dev's review, scheduled scans (config cadence). · st:/ Protocol=`THREAT MODEL (marketplace/threat-model → THREAT_MODEL.md) scopes the run \· -> RECON: partition the attack surface (parallel finders explore different areas, not the same bug) \· -> FIND: detect by the target's signal, PRIORITIZED BY STACK (see assets/detection-classes-web-llm-2026-07.md): \· • Interpreted (Python/JS/TS) = static taint + the web detection classes (injection/IDOR/SSRF/secrets…) \· • LLM/agent code = the LLM detection classes (prompt injection, insecure output, excessive agency, RAG poisoning) — the fleet defends itself` · in=**Aim before you shoot.** scan without current threat model scoping (build/refresh imported skill first). unscoped scan downgraded "exploratory," labeled, findings carry lower triage confidence. **Static first, always stack-appropriate.** Read/write static review runs first unsandboxed (it never executes target code imported threat-model skill's Step preamble governs). Use detection signals `assets/detection-classes-web-llm-2026-07.md` stack play: web LLM classes primary detectors deployment (agents Python/JS/TS LLM); harness's ASAN detector native-code-only. Expect false positives non-canary targets; that's what verification for. **Execution sandbox.** Any finding step builds runs target code executes inside gVisor-pattern sandbox egress restricted Claude API charter's Rail which literally generalized harness. Outside sandbox fails closed; override department (the harness's `--override` exposed). **Verification separate grader.** finding isn't real until fresh environment (that finder never touched) reproduces proof-of-concept alone. kills "the finder convinced itself" failure mode security analogue quinn's evidence-not-claims rule. **Triage against threat model, vibes.** Rank model's impact×likelihood; exclude bugs deliberately-vulnerable test/fixture code (the harness's canary lesson); recalibrate severity business's assets. Findings map threat IDs finding threat either threat-model gap (update it) noise. **Route, don't hoard.** real finding goes three places: owning builder (dev's domain routing), quinn's intake (it's gate input future regression-map entry), verified-patching fix. aegis finds coordinates fix; silently sit findings. **CVE intake ops.** maintenance-hygiene's above-patch-level CVEs enter seeded findings (evidence attached), scoped against threat model, triaged like any joint work ops's boundary. · of=`## Vuln Pipeline: [target] — scoped by [THREAT_MODEL.md ref] \· Mode: static / execution(sandboxed) \· Recon partitions: [n] \· Findings: [n raw → n verified → n unique] \· Dropped: [fixture/false-positive counts] \· Top by threat-model rank: [id \· threat-id \· severity \· owner] \· Routed: → quinn intake [ref] \· → verified-patching [refs] \· → owners [list]` · of=Findings follow `assets/findings-schema.md` (adapted harness's VULN-FINDINGS/TRIAGE shape). Summary user: · pr=**Aim before you shoot** threat-model-scoped scans, explicitly-labeled exploratory ones., **Static first; execution sandbox, fail closed** Rail departmental override., **A separate grader verifies** finder doesn't get grade crash., **Triage against threat model** impact×likelihood business's assets, raw counts., **Every finding routed** owner quinn intake patch; aegis never hoards findings., **False positives expected killed verification** noise upstream fine; unverified findings shipping downstream not. · f=sandbox available execution-mode finding DISABLED (fail closed); static-only runs proceed, labeled, note execution-verification unavailable. Never run target code unsandboxed "just check.", Harness connected (autonomous pipeline absent) interactive skills' discipline still applies manually (scope static review verify careful re-analysis triage route); depth degrades loudly, method holds., Stack ported (reference detector C/C++) static review threat-model reasoning carry run; /customize port business's language/vuln-class flagged task., Finding disputed false positive re-verify fresh environment; verification verdict stands over opinion. · b:with Other Skills=**assets/detection-classes-web-llm-2026-07.md** concrete find-layer interpreted LLM stacks (web OWASP Top LLM OWASP Top 2025), Python/JS/TS signals. aegis's real discovery teeth actual stack; harness pipeline native-code path., **marketplace/threat-model** (imported) scopes run; skill consumes THREAT_MODEL.md never re-implements threat modeling., **secure-code-review** (sibling) human-paced deep read specific risky diff; breadth scan across surface. They meet triage., **verified-patching** (sibling) takes routed findings produces verified fixes; finding closed there., **cypher** (adversary, built): cypher attacks continuously files findings quinn; aegis's pipeline defensive discovery. Overlap (both find bugs) deliberate redundancy; cypher's Rail cage cypher's concern, skill's., **quinn/charter-enforcement**: owns sandbox skill's execution mode requires; findings enter quinn's intake become regression-map entries close., **ops/maintenance-hygiene**: CVE handoff source; joint above-patch-level severity.